MAMELODI Sundowns coach Pitso Mosimane says he will use this weekend’s Telkom Knockout quarterfinal clash with Baroka FC as a platform to help his players regain some of their confidence, especially in front of goal. The game is scheduled for Polokwane’s Peter Mokaba Stadium on Saturday (3pm). Mosimane is concerned as his charges have failed to score an average of two goals per game as was the norm last season. CONTINUED ONPAGE 29